<plot>Musical biography of Fats Waller. Ken Prymus, and the actors and actresses from 1980 off-Broadway production of "Ain't Misbehavin'", in a portrait of Fats Waller, his life and the music he wrote or made popular. With rare "soundies" film and photographs. Selections performed include "T'aint Nobody's Business", "Ain't Misbehaving", "What Did I Do to Be So Black and Blue?", "The Joint's Jumpin'", "Honeysuckle Rose" and "Your Feet's Too Big."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?190983</url></doc>
